Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard stories, but I never
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,imagined it would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.90,0:00:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.16,0:00:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This place holds secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.51,0:00:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,An ordinary Tuesday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The house near the Savannah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.77,0:00:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,River woke up slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.45,0:00:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The way old houses do, carrying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.17,0:00:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the habit of breathing before
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.77,0:00:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,their people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.87,0:00:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of dawn came through
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the crack in the curtains in a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,thin strip
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and settled on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,her shoulder, and Jago Quint
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.81,0:00:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,stood there looking at that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.35,0:00:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,shoulder for longer than was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.51,0:00:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.61,0:00:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena slept on her side, one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.41,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,hand opened near her
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.65,0:00:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,face, like someone who had left
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.15,0:00:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a question
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.63,0:00:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,half-assed, and decided to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.09,0:00:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,finish asking at the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.15,0:00:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheet had slipped down to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,her waist, and the light caught
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.15,0:00:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the loose strands of her hair
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.47,0:00:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which still smelled of the soap
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.83,0:00:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.21,0:00:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He got up without a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.11,0:00:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,His body knew this ritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.99,0:00:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting out of bed without
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.15,0:00:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,waking the one who stayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.77,0:00:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a calm inside him that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.35,0:00:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,still scared him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.51,0:00:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months after she'd moved
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.76,0:00:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,into that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.47,0:00:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That was love he'd discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.21,0:00:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.55,0:01:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was something else a small
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,dread,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.57,0:01:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,almost decorative that lived
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.99,0:01:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath his ribcage and beat
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.41,0:01:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,along with his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.91,0:01:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought he knew how to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.24,0:01:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.69,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A man who survived what he'd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,survived, learns to tame his own
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.18,0:01:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.87,0:01:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He went down the stairs stepping
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.20,0:01:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,on the side of the wood that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.37,0:01:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't creak.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.29,0:01:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitchen was still cold, with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.15,0:01:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that stale air of June mornings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.95,0:01:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that hadn't decided
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.05,0:01:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they were warm or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.75,0:01:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned on the kettle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.73,0:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Measured out her coffee like
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.23,0:01:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,someone writing a sentence he
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.79,0:01:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,already knew by heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.45,0:01:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Two scoops of grounds, water
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.11,0:01:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that hadn't fully boiled, a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.71,0:01:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,little less than the usual
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.25,0:01:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ratio,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.15,0:01:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because Roenah liked her coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.63,0:01:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,milder at the start of the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.49,0:01:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as if the morning needed to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,permission before coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.89,0:01:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell rose slowly through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.29,0:01:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.35,0:01:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something in it he
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,could never quite name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.89,0:01:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't the coffee itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.63,0:01:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was what the smell stood for.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.55,0:01:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She was still there and she'd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.90,0:01:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.37,0:01:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a thought he avoided
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,at that hour, and the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.51,0:01:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,showed up anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.83,0:01:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If she ever vanished from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.31,0:01:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the smell of coffee would tear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.70,0:01:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,him apart with devastating
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.90,0:01:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.03,0:02:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He stirred the spoon slowly and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.76,0:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,brushed the thought aside with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.44,0:02:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the same gesture you'd use to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.06,0:02:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,wave off a polite fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.75,0:02:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The male came early.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.29,0:02:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline, the personal assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.87,0:02:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,delivered the envelope at the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.34,0:02:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,side door with the discrete
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.71,0:02:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,punctuality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.27,0:02:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Gope de Léfour.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.03,0:02:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There were three letters from
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the office, one from the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.25,0:02:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,management of one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.25,0:02:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.71,0:02:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and a cream-coloured envelope,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.65,0:02:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,no return address,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a dress to Roenah Pike in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.75,0:02:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal handwriting of a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.03,0:02:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.11,0:02:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at some respectable institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.23,0:02:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He recognized the letterhead in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.59,0:02:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the upper corner before he even
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.95,0:02:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,looked properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.23,0:02:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood there for a second with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.57,0:02:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the envelope between his
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.41,0:02:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling the specific weight of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.95,0:02:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,quality paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.19,0:02:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take this one. He said,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.11,0:02:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,low.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He tucked the envelope into the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,inside pocket of his jacket,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.05,0:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he were putting away an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.36,0:02:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,important document he'd remember
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.80,0:02:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to hand over later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.65,0:02:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew he wouldn't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd already decided not to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.86,0:02:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,remember before he even finished
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.70,0:02:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.95,0:02:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst part was that his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.42,0:02:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,had made the move without
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:02:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,consulting him,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:02:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with an old efficiency he
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.85,0:03:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,recognized as his own and didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.60,0:03:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,like recognizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.59,0:03:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.99,0:03:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The two exchanged a brief
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,greeting, and the assistant left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.07,0:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the same way he'd come in,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is steps muffled by the runner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When Roenah came down, coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.13,0:03:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was served in two cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She appeared in the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.34,0:03:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,doorway in a long night gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hair loosely pinned up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,rubbing her eye with a closed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fist like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.39,0:03:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The morning sun was coming in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.67,0:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,now through the side window,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.43,0:03:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and drew a golden square on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.05,0:03:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,wooden floor between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.59,0:03:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked up and the small
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,decorative dread settled back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath his ribcage quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You got up early?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She remarked, her voice still
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.78,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thick with sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't sleep with you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,breathing so beautifully like
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.50,0:03:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go answered, and his mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.69,0:03:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,almost smiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.13,0:03:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.15,0:03:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a short slightly husky
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.65,0:03:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,laugh, the kind he collected
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.10,0:03:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,inside without admitting he
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.49,0:03:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,collected them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.47,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She sat on the stool at the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen island, took the cup
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with both hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:03:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and smelled it before drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:03:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the way she did every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.85,0:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,her eyes closing for half a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.19,0:04:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,second over the steam,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a gesture so hers that he
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,already knew it by heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.95,0:04:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He watched without seeming to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.01,0:04:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you expecting anything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.23,0:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked, and the tone was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,casual in that practiced way,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.47,0:04:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rowing a thought for a second
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,her eyes still on the cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,an answer, she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That conversation I told you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about last week, she looked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember, he answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.37,0:04:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You remembered?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.39,0:04:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In his pocket he had exactly the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.13,0:04:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,answer she was waiting for,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the answer was generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.51,0:04:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer would take her
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.77,0:04:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that house for six
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.85,0:04:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,months.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The pocket weighed on him in a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,specific way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He drank his own coffee and said
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena looked at him for a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.18,0:04:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,second longer than her usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.89,0:04:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then she looked at her own
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rest of the morning ran
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,along beautifully,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the way their mornings usually
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.73,0:04:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At noon, Silas Ashford was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for Jago at the office
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.71,0:04:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in downtown Savannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.31,0:04:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyer had a way of sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in chairs that didn't belong to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.14,0:04:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,him as if they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Legs crossed, one finger resting
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.12,0:05:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,against his temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the expressionless face he wore
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.25,0:05:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when he brought bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The air conditioning in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.27,0:05:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was set too high,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.63,0:05:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the artificial chill clashed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.09,0:05:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with the heat coming in through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.51,0:05:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the wide windows overlooking the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.97,0:05:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,square.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.93,0:05:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Short lunch, Silas announced
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.61,0:05:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jago walked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Short why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.27,0:05:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what I've got to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.53,0:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you doesn't go well with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.49,0:05:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago closed the door behind him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.12,0:05:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he sat down on the other side of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.63,0:05:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The two had known each other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.77,0:05:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,long enough to skip the run
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's asking questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.14,0:05:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas said without raising his
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.68,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,again in three different places,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,discrete questions, the kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.16,0:05:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,trained person asks,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.75,0:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the questions come too close
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to what we agreed to never let
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.62,0:05:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone get close to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.73,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago didn't move, inside the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,decorative dread grew an inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.73,0:05:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked, not yet, but they pay
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,well, and they pay with money
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that leaves no trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.75,0:05:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That interest me more than the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.14,0:05:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.77,0:05:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago looked at the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a line of silence the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:05:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,two of them respected,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:05:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind built over years of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:05:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,loyalty,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.13,0:06:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He always waited with that stone
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,patience he charged
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,dearly for by the hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.31,0:06:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Double the security at the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,house, Jago said finally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.07,0:06:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina can't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas kept looking at him a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,second longer than necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.37,0:06:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago, she can't know Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.97,0:06:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyer ran his tongue along
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the inside corner of his cheek,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.29,0:06:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a small gesture he made when he
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to say something,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.15,0:06:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and chose not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.39,0:06:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he nodded in that short dry
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.44,0:06:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,way of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that envelope, Silas asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.97,0:06:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,did the answer come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.49,0:06:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago didn't answer right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.31,0:06:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He tapped his thumb lightly on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the tabletop once twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.77,0:06:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It came.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.87,0:06:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to deliver it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.41,0:06:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.11,0:06:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago looked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something in his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.54,0:06:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that Silas had known long before
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.86,0:06:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.17,0:06:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The same thing that lived in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.61,0:06:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that gaze ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Silas had hoped for a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,while had gotten better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.45,0:06:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When I figure out how, Silas
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,nodded,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but his face didn't agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.49,0:06:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The two finished lunch in decent
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:06:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,silence with the noise from the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,square
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in muffled through the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.45,0:07:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.33,0:07:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jago left the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the cream envelope was still
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,weighing in the inside pocket of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,his jacket,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he had for the first time in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.75,0:07:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a long time, a brief urge to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.59,0:07:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,tear it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.73,0:07:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina spent the afternoon in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.89,0:07:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the living room of the house
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.01,0:07:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She was rereading some old
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,worknotes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,things she kept in a hardcover
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,folder that sat on a shelf in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,plain sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.25,0:07:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,no hiding place at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.49,0:07:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd learned to value that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.03,0:07:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,transparency the way people do,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who have already lost someone by
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.82,0:07:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,hiding too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The afternoon light came in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.50,0:07:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,slanted through the half open
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.13,0:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,blinds,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and striped the rug in golden
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.99,0:07:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside the river made its usual
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gentle sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.05,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the living room phone rang at a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.63,0:07:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,little past five.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.93,0:07:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither he'd gone to the market
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.17,0:07:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with Fielen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.25,0:07:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago hadn't come back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.25,0:07:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.43,0:07:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Quint residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.43,0:07:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The way she always answered,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.99,0:07:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,half joking with the formality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other end, a full second
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.78,0:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:07:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a man's voice horse with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.41,0:07:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,age and with something harder to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:07:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,name,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.53,0:08:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,good afternoon I need to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.77,0:08:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with Mr. Quint.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.93,0:08:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not in at the moment, can I
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.36,0:08:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,take a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Another silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.99,0:08:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She heard the man breathe as if
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he were weighing every word
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.48,0:08:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,before letting it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina, a well-trained
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.10,0:08:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,journalist,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.15,0:08:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,began paying attention with her
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.69,0:08:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,whole body,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.69,0:08:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,without yet knowing why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something in that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.59,0:08:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,silence that wasn't in decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.57,0:08:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the man coughed lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.07,0:08:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him it's about kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.93,0:08:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina stopped breathing for a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.67,0:08:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.49,0:08:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because of the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.05,0:08:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The name still meant nothing to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.95,0:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She stopped because of the way
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the man said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.41,0:08:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Like someone handing over a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.61,0:08:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,password,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he knows will open a door that's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.63,0:08:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,been locked for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.43,0:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit, she repeated slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and her voice came out more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.56,0:08:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral than she was feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.43,0:08:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,May I ask who's calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.61,0:08:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The man was already answering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when the front door slammed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.35,0:08:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick steps in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Quicker than Jago's step usually
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.19,0:08:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,was at the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He walked into the room with his
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.20,0:08:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,meeting posture still in his
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:08:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,body,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.13,0:09:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and stopped walking when he saw
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the phone in her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.91,0:09:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She watched the colour drain
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.62,0:09:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from his face in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.57,0:09:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was something she'd never
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.05,0:09:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,seen before in that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No anger, no practice surprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,just a physical animal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.97,0:09:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,whiteness,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,rising from his chin to his
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,forehead in seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.15,0:09:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as if someone had flipped a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.79,0:09:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.73,0:09:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked, his voice too low for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.36,0:09:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She held out the receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.33,0:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago took it, brought it to his
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.99,0:09:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,listened for two seconds, closed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.98,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,his eyes once,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.31,0:09:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a single blink longer than
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.70,0:09:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of gesture that isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,reflex its decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.57,0:09:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then said just one sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.59,0:09:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't call this number.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.11,0:09:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He kept his hand on the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for a length of time she counted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,inside her own chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.99,0:09:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,beat by beat, Roena looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.13,0:09:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She knew that man in her body,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.99,0:09:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in his smell, in the way he ran
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,his thumb under his eye when he
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.24,0:09:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:09:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd never seen him white like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.75,0:09:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.19,0:09:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd never seen him need
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,support just to stay standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.43,0:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago, he didn't answer right
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.91,0:10:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.73,0:10:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked, with the trained calm
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,her profession had given her as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.11,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.99,0:10:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked up, and that was when
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.86,0:10:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,she saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But the first time since the two
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.08,0:10:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of them had met,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.05,0:10:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,she saw him decide to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.65,0:10:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a quick decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.85,0:10:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She saw the moment before it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.49,0:10:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the instant when he could still
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.03,0:10:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,choose the other path.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.41,0:10:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,An old employee, Jago said,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.65,0:10:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,drunk probably got the wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.27,0:10:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.99,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept looking at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.47,0:10:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He held her gaze with the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.61,0:10:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,composure of someone who'd spent
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,his whole life holding gays,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't afford to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.67,0:10:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew inside that she knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, he wanted her to let it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.77,0:10:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He said a name, Roena said,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.93,0:10:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and her voice came out very low
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,almost gentle,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which was the way she used when
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.82,0:10:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the question wasn't gentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.77,0:10:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago swallowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.93,0:10:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.65,0:10:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't blink.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He carried his body to the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sideboard next to the sofa,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,rested his hand on the wood as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.15,0:10:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,if he needed something solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.89,0:10:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and spoke looking at the river
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.22,0:10:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,through the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:10:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,his back to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena stood where she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.83,0:11:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,near the big window there was a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.45,0:11:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.23,0:11:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the one in the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.38,0:11:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,mansions main hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.71,0:11:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,brought here when they moved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.25,0:11:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She had now six months of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.57,0:11:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at that chair without
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.10,0:11:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding why no
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,one ever sat in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.55,0:11:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the seat was always turned
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.90,0:11:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,slightly toward the river,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as if waiting for someone who
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.87,0:11:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,knew where they'd arrive from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.47,0:11:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the chair, looked
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.34,0:11:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,at Jago's back,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at the chair again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.03,0:11:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the chair for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.69,0:11:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,had a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.83,0:11:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The name was short, short, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.28,0:11:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.03,0:11:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It had only three letters, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.53,0:11:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,had slipped down the phone line
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.07,0:11:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,like a poorly tied
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,secret, spoken by a horse voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.57,0:11:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't repeat it out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.43,0:11:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very good at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.11,0:11:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That night Roena didn't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She lay looking at the bedroom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,ceiling,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.33,0:11:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,listening to his breathing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,beside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That breathing she knew better
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.95,0:11:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than her own,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that she could tell when it was
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.25,0:11:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,real sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.01,0:11:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it was faked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.51,0:11:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That night for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.90,0:11:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,she couldn't read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.13,0:12:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside, the river ran with its
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,usual soft sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.33,0:12:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,indifferent to what was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.40,0:12:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,happening inside that beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.85,0:12:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside her chest, an empty chair
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,had begun to creak.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.67,0:12:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter two, tenderness isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.05,0:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sun came into the bedroom in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,morning, as if nothing had
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.19,0:12:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.07,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jago moved in bed the way he
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,always did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.77,0:12:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His hand seeking her waist
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath the sheet,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.55,0:12:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,his face pressing into the nape
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of her neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.15,0:12:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the short kiss at the spot where
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,her hair began.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.45,0:12:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena lay still, eyes closed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and received it all with her
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.33,0:12:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.99,0:12:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,His warmth was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.23,0:12:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of his arm was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was easier to stay quiet a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,second longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and let her body believe in what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,her mind hadn't yet resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.33,0:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she turned over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.81,0:12:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.29,0:12:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The call yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.61,0:12:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He opened his eyes with a staged
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,laziness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.45,0:12:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She saw the staging.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.83,0:12:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was quick, almost
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.08,0:12:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,imperceptible, but she saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:12:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd learn to see the small
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:12:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,things in him before she'd learn
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.23,0:12:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.29,0:13:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you my love, it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.74,0:13:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.27,0:13:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You went white.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago smiled with half his mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.11,0:13:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that small smile he reserved for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.92,0:13:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,diffusing difficult situations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in boardrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He raised his hand and tucked a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,strand of her hair behind her
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with a calculated lightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.29,0:13:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A gesture that had always worked
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.83,0:13:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.63,0:13:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One she herself had loved in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,those first months,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.49,0:13:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when she still couldn't tell
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.67,0:13:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,genuine tenderness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.43,0:13:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from the tenderness that served
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as a curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.09,0:13:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't, he said, his voice low
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and firm,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you were against the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.77,0:13:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at him in silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.11,0:13:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A pause of three, four seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.43,0:13:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enough for any guilty person to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.91,0:13:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fill the emptiness with more
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,words.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't fill it, he was too
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.06,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,good for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He leaned in, kissed the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.49,0:13:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of her mouth with a tenderness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.99,0:13:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that was real and at the same
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.37,0:13:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,time evasive about everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and spoke against her skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.13,0:13:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.61,0:13:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.95,0:13:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She kissed him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.29,0:13:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Short, got up, went to shower
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.34,0:13:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And while the water fell too hot
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:13:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on her shoulders,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.41,0:14:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,she thought for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in plain terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.89,0:14:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a sentence that bothered her a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.18,0:14:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.21,0:14:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenderness and truth are not the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.37,0:14:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.37,0:14:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,She stayed under the water
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.66,0:14:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,longer than she needed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The bathroom smelled of the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,citrus soap
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.11,0:14:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago had started buying for her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.74,0:14:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,when he noticed which one she
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.27,0:14:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.15,0:14:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One more detail he memorized,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.23,0:14:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one more gesture she no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,knew how to receive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.23,0:14:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She came down dressed to go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.39,0:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Linen pants, a light-colored
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,blouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.97,0:14:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A small bag she used when she
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,went downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.89,0:14:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago was in the kitchen reading
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.57,0:14:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,something on the tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.81,0:14:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with a cup of coffee in front of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,him that must have been
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.72,0:14:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,half-loop warm by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.19,0:14:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at her with that gaze
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.53,0:14:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that crossed the room without
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.79,0:14:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,needing distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.05,0:14:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She founded amusing, not the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.94,0:14:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his old tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.65,0:14:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The one she thought had been
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.87,0:14:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,left behind since they'd gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.73,0:14:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months earlier to live
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.85,0:14:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,together there near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Downtown, by a couple things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.11,0:14:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo arrives today, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.49,0:14:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.19,0:14:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He set down the tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.93,0:15:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm driving myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.47,0:15:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He nodded as if he were
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.68,0:15:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.55,0:15:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He reached out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Took a hand on the cold marble
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.15,0:15:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,counter,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.21,0:15:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,squeezed it lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.43,0:15:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,His fingers wrapping around hers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with the ease of someone who
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.67,0:15:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,already knew every knuckle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.49,0:15:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She went out the side door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.13,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She walked along the stone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hallway to the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.65,0:15:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,took the keys off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.45,0:15:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The air outside smelled of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.91,0:15:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,river's dampness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and of some neighbouring garden
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.35,0:15:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that must have had Jasmine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was early enough that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.52,0:15:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah's heat hadn't yet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,weighed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.73,0:15:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When she opened the electric
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.69,0:15:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,two men in suits were standing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.18,0:15:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,outside next to a dark car she
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.67,0:15:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't recognize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.11,0:15:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't seem like a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.83,0:15:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They seemed like scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The scenery of another kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,house, not hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them approached with a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.81,0:15:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,smile that was too polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.49,0:15:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Pike, good morning, will be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.97,0:15:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.89,0:15:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena blinked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Going with me, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,House orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.79,0:15:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Security.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.77,0:15:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.11,0:15:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at the other one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.51,0:15:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither of them seemed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:15:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.47,0:16:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither of them seemed to expect
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.92,0:16:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,her to argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That, more than anything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.45,0:16:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was what bothered her,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that they derived ready for the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,normalcy of a situation she
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.61,0:16:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't authorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.05,0:16:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask for security.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, with a calm that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.27,0:16:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't easy to maintain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.05,0:16:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to ask, Mom, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.54,0:16:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,already been arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.07,0:16:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She stood for a second on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.39,0:16:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,stone pavement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.07,0:16:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside the house, behind her,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.76,0:16:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.13,0:16:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago was on the tablet with the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,lukewarm cup and he knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.25,0:16:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd given the order the day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.57,0:16:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,before at the downtown office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.43,0:16:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And he knew the exact second
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd meet those two men at the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.32,0:16:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At that very moment, sitting in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.75,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he swallowed some coffee that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was too cold to cover his own
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.80,0:16:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.71,0:16:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,His hand pressing lightly on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.40,0:16:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,tablet for no reason at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.17,0:16:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena didn't make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.79,0:16:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She simply said, all right, she
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,got into her car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.99,0:16:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let their car follow behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.33,0:16:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She drove to downtown Savannah
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.73,0:16:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with both hands on the wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the silence inside the car
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so vast that she turned on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.95,0:17:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Found it unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.59,0:17:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Turned it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.73,0:17:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A hand stayed on the leather of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.12,0:17:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.97,0:17:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and she looked out the window at
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the old Magnolia's lining the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.11,0:17:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,White and heavy from so much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.47,0:17:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,blooming
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought that some beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,things were also suffocating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.77,0:17:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo Trent showed up on time at
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the old cafe in the historic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.74,0:17:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,district,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.19,0:17:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with a bag too big for anything
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.94,0:17:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,she could possibly need there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.91,0:17:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And an expression Rowena
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.30,0:17:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,recognized from far off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.05,0:17:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression of someone who'd
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.54,0:17:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,flown three hours
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.35,0:17:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to give a dose of reality to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.05,0:17:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,someone she loved very much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and who was in need of hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.31,0:17:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.87,0:17:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Row, Marlo, they hugged the way
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.76,0:17:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd hugged for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.57,0:17:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,tight without ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.23,0:17:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo rubbing her hand twice on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.62,0:17:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,her back with that energy of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who'd arrived to fix
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.03,0:17:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The cafe smelled of cinnamon and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.93,0:17:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,burnt coffee from an old
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.35,0:17:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dark wooden tables had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,marks from years of cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.63,0:17:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They sat near the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo ordered black coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena, a cappuccino.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.75,0:17:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Across the street the dark car
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:17:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,parked with professional
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.08,0:17:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.15,0:18:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two yours, Marlo pointed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.09,0:18:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with her chin, no filter at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.59,0:18:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the houses, the houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.15,0:18:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Marlo raised a eyebrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.63,0:18:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo had an eyebrow that asked
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.09,0:18:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,whole questions on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.32,0:18:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,without needing anything more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Row, don't start.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.21,0:18:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Row, love doesn't treat you like
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.95,0:18:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.09,0:18:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a short laugh a little
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,awkward but honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.83,0:18:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And she felt along with it a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,good pang.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.15,0:18:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The pang of someone being
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.51,0:18:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,reminded of herself by someone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who'd known her before all of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.72,0:18:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.25,0:18:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They talked for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.91,0:18:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo talked about the newsroom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about the new editor who'd
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.07,0:18:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,reorganized everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.81,0:18:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,About the people who still asked
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.55,0:18:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,about Rowena now and then with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.17,0:18:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that mix of curiosity and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.53,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,respect
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes just before being
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.49,0:18:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena listened and wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,feel a clean kind of longing,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.95,0:18:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomplicated, but the longing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that arrived had an uneven edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.75,0:18:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At some point, out of old
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,reflex, she took the recorder
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.05,0:18:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from her bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A small, silver recorder that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:18:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,she carried out of a habit of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.50,0:18:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,more than six years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,always in the side pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.67,0:19:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the device in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.26,0:19:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,palm of her hand as if she
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.59,0:19:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't sure when it had ended
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.13,0:19:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.83,0:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She put it back without pressing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a single button.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.57,0:19:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo saw everything always had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you now journalist?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked, with the corner of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,her mouth croaked in a way that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.98,0:19:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was both a question and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.23,0:19:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena laughed for real this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.62,0:19:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.31,0:19:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A bigger laugh that arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.62,0:19:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.01,0:19:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman waiting for an answer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.72,0:19:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that never comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.23,0:19:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.31,0:19:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A job offer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.53,0:19:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent it last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.09,0:19:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I still haven't gotten any
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo kept looking at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.57,0:19:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She held the cup with both hands
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and waited a second longer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,before speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.79,0:19:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That second rowing a new.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The second that came before the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.26,0:19:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,sentences that stayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.97,0:19:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Row.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.73,0:19:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.51,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it didn't come?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.31,0:19:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena stopped the cappuccino
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The cup hung suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The heat rising to her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.53,0:19:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:19:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:19:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo deflected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.07,0:19:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And looked at the dark car
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,across the street with an
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,expression that was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.75,0:20:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sentence stayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo knew how to put sentences
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.44,0:20:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the air the way they'd hang
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.95,0:20:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.99,0:20:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one stayed the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.09,0:20:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.47,0:20:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of the whole afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.41,0:20:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena returned to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,near the river in the late
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.71,0:20:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With savanna's golden light
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.06,0:20:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,striking the paving stones from
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.51,0:20:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And a thin mist rising from the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.21,0:20:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,river as it always did when the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,heat began to give way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.63,0:20:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The two men followed behind in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.27,0:20:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,professional silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.01,0:20:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego was still at the downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.53,0:20:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,office.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.31,0:20:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The house was quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.37,0:20:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Only neither in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutting something with that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.98,0:20:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,silent precision of hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.63,0:20:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the smell of rosemary coming
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.31,0:20:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from some pot that had been on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the stove for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.45,0:20:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena went into Jego's private
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.17,0:20:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,study with an excuse she'd
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,prepared for herself while still
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.45,0:20:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She needed that old contract
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.78,0:20:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from the house renovation work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.59,0:20:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The carpenter had asked for a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.92,0:20:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,copy of the original
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.83,0:20:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,specification.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.09,0:20:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a polite lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.59,0:20:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind you tell yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.67,0:20:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,before doing what you were going
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.99,0:21:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to do anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She opened the first drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.73,0:21:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Office papers all in order
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.53,0:21:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,labeled with the precision of a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.68,0:21:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,man who tolerated chaos on no
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.70,0:21:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.05,0:21:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Second drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.17,0:21:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.09,0:21:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thin folders with dates and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.51,0:21:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Third drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A cream-coloured envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.19,0:21:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No return address.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.67,0:21:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,With her name in the center in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.30,0:21:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.29,0:21:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Typewritten handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.87,0:21:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her head in the upper right
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.37,0:21:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.23,0:21:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Winslow foundation for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,independent journalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The envelope was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.51,0:21:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She stood still.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The study itself went still
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.38,0:21:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The dark shelves, the books
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,lined up by size.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.67,0:21:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The narrow window that looked
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.12,0:21:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out onto the side garden with
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the moss on the stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.27,0:21:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hands went strangely quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.47,0:21:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She took the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She pulled out the contents
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.26,0:21:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,carefully, as if the paper might
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.98,0:21:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,confirm something she already
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.54,0:21:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.11,0:21:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But didn't yet want to name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Two sheets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.21,0:21:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The first was the formal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.24,0:21:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.39,0:21:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A job offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.09,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A series of long investigative
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:21:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,reports full ground complete
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.42,0:22:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomy over the topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.35,0:22:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An offer that would bring her
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.60,0:22:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,career back to life from
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.45,0:22:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At the exact point where she'd
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.75,0:22:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,left off before Savannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.69,0:22:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Before everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.05,0:22:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The second sheet was a carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.70,0:22:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.47,0:22:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.63,0:22:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Dated 10 days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Serz.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.73,0:22:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank you for your generous
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.97,0:22:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.27,0:22:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time Miss Pike is not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.71,0:22:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,available to take on new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.89,0:22:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,professional commitments.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.13,0:22:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We renew our thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.43,0:22:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A signature at the bottom in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.80,0:22:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.03,0:22:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The same handwriting that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.99,0:22:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared in the notes he left
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,her in the kitchen in the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as the contract she
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.48,0:22:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,signed alongside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.85,0:22:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The same one she'd learned to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.30,0:22:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize before even reading
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.74,0:22:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what was written.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.07,0:22:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.57,0:22:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna kept looking at the sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.87,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for a length of time she
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.07,0:22:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Her body didn't tremble.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.57,0:22:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Her body went very still.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.43,0:22:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the stillness was heavier
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.98,0:22:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,than any tremor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.27,0:22:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna put the envelope back in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.03,0:22:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Closed it with the same care
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.76,0:22:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.91,0:22:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She left the private study
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.13,0:22:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,without taking the carpenters
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.49,0:22:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.29,0:22:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't need the contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.95,0:23:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She never had.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.13,0:23:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She went to the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.63,0:23:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She sat on the sofa without
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.10,0:23:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,turning on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.71,0:23:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The afternoon had closed into
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.12,0:23:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that dark blue of early night
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that came fast in Savannah's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.89,0:23:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.71,0:23:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the room filled with a warm
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.25,0:23:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,dimness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side next to the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.30,0:23:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,big window.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.29,0:23:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The empty chair was in its usual
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.96,0:23:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.63,0:23:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With the last light of day
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.84,0:23:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching only the backrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.09,0:23:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the chair for a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.01,0:23:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.05,0:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Two stories she thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.29,0:23:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them has a short old name
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.92,0:23:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that no one pronounces inside
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.39,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.29,0:23:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The other has his handwriting on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a sheet that answered for her
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.32,0:23:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,without her knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.97,0:23:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Jago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.35,0:23:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.13,0:23:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.95,0:23:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stay hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.33,0:23:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.73,0:23:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She closed her eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.11,0:23:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She held her voice in the right
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.60,0:23:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.21,0:23:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That exact place where the voice
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.08,0:23:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,stops trembling and becomes just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.95,0:23:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.53,0:23:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.85,0:23:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.93,0:23:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.87,0:23:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.75,0:23:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept the phone in her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.61,0:23:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The heat of the device against
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.03,0:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,her palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.99,0:23:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside the river ran with that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.56,0:24:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,low constant sound she'd learned
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.19,0:24:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to find calming
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.95,0:24:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and that now sounded different.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.09,0:24:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The empty chair waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.93,0:24:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time in six
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.43,0:24:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,months,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.15,0:24:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena Pike felt inside her own
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.79,0:24:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.57,0:24:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The low firm creek of a decision
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.28,0:24:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning to be made.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.23,0:24:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 3 The Name No One Said.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.13,0:24:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The cream envelope sat on the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.82,0:24:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,table between them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.87,0:24:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as if it weighed more than the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.39,0:24:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,wood holding it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena had waited all day to set
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.30,0:24:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it down there
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.93,0:24:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at the exact spot where he
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.34,0:24:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,usually left his keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.99,0:24:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She chose the dining room table
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.56,0:24:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was the only room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.98,0:24:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jago couldn't lean on a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.45,0:24:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,work object.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.49,0:24:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No paper, no pen, no phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.93,0:24:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just him, her and his
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.09,0:24:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,handwriting betraying his
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.47,0:24:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.81,0:24:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago came in after eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.47,0:24:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He took off his jacket with the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.86,0:24:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,slowness of someone who already
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.25,0:24:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,knew what he'd find.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.15,0:24:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The house near the Savannah
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.48,0:24:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,River smelled of jasmine from
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.91,0:24:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the garden outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.33,0:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,An out of season sweetness that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.10,0:24:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,only worsened the sensation that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.92,0:24:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the air was breathing on its
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.97,0:24:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.35,0:24:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't ask what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.07,0:25:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside he felt a lying sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.74,0:25:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,form before he could stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.51,0:25:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to tell you and in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.95,0:25:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the same instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.17,0:25:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,new it was false.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.57,0:25:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.77,0:25:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If she hadn't found it, that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.13,0:25:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,paper would have died at the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.50,0:25:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of that drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.05,0:25:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena, his voice came out too
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.69,0:25:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,controlled to be sincere.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.05,0:25:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.15,0:25:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She crossed her arms over her
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.59,0:25:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,linen dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.57,0:25:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.67,0:25:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The yellow light of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.72,0:25:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,chandelier fell between them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.01,0:25:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,like a border.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.13,0:25:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exactly what it looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.70,0:25:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.43,0:25:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He breathed in deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.91,0:25:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The cold panic settled between
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,one river and another.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.83,0:25:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That old cold he knew from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.44,0:25:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,another night, 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.41,0:25:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He swallowed twice before he
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.73,0:25:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,managed to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.97,0:25:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.63,0:25:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,From a job offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.89,0:25:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,From an offer that was going to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.28,0:25:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,take you away from Savannah for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.68,0:25:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.17,0:25:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena smiled without joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.69,0:25:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the decision to go or stay
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.61,0:25:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,was yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.71,0:25:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He opened his mouth and found no
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.19,0:25:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.95,0:25:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She continued lower because the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.59,0:25:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,low voice hurt more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.05,0:25:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You answered for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.05,0:25:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You said, thank you for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.89,0:25:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You declined for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.51,0:26:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Each sentence fell like a small
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.02,0:26:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,stone into the bottom of a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.28,0:26:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.03,0:26:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you brought me
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.89,0:26:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.91,0:26:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.87,0:26:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.59,0:26:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She raised her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.01,0:26:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And her hand was trembling and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.50,0:26:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,she hated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.49,0:26:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to ask me for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.88,0:26:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.11,0:26:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is the one thing you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.57,0:26:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't ask for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.39,0:26:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You had six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.97,0:26:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He took a step toward her.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.63,0:26:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She took a step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.05,0:26:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a small movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.63,0:26:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But he felt as if he'd been
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.89,0:26:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,shoved against the opposite wall
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.39,0:26:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.47,0:26:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside something in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.31,0:26:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The part that was always certain
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.39,0:26:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,began to crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.79,0:26:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He watched her mouth pronounce
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.57,0:26:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the next sentence before he
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.18,0:26:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.83,0:26:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is Kit?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.03,0:26:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The name fell to the dining room
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.65,0:26:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,floor and stayed there gleaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.75,0:26:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago looked at the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.03,0:26:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.59,0:26:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at the window that faced
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.19,0:26:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the dark river outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.91,0:26:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.15,0:26:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And his silence was the first
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.79,0:26:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,real confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.37,0:26:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Jago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.59,0:26:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She went up the stairs slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.53,0:26:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood beside the table for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.87,0:26:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,too long listening to her
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.02,0:26:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,footsteps disappear into the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.31,0:26:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,upstairs hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.61,0:26:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he sat in the nearest chair
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.27,0:27:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,elbows on his knees and stared
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.82,0:27:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at his own envelope as if
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.11,0:27:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the paper were capable of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.42,0:27:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,answering for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.73,0:27:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena didn't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.11,0:27:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She spent the small hours with
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.45,0:27:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,her eyes open at the ceiling of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.84,0:27:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.51,0:27:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That room she'd never entered
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.02,0:27:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,before and where the sheets
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.43,0:27:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,smelled of forgotten lavender.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.43,0:27:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She mentally repeated the list
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.05,0:27:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of things she knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.41,0:27:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The name, the chair, the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.88,0:27:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.97,0:27:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Udora's remark about a laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.60,0:27:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.05,0:27:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The payments she hadn't yet
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.43,0:27:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,traced.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.23,0:27:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The envelope answered in his
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.53,0:27:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There were two stories being
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.75,0:27:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.43,0:27:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She needed to unravel both.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.45,0:27:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning before the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.93,0:27:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,rose fully, she called a taxi
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.41,0:27:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.57,0:27:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't ask for a house car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.41,0:27:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't tell Fielen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.43,0:27:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She put on the plainest clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.31,0:27:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,she had and went out the side
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.07,0:27:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,door and no guard saw her,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.87,0:27:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because no guard expected her to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.33,0:27:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,leave before six in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.39,0:27:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas Ashford's office was in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.01,0:27:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,downtown Savannah in an old
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.52,0:27:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,townhouse with tall windows
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.03,0:27:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and a permanent smell of coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.88,0:27:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and old paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.19,0:27:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun hadn't yet warm the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.47,0:27:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sidewalk when she climbed the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.85,0:27:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.67,0:28:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas answered the door himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.67,0:28:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even ask what she
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.73,0:28:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.39,0:28:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He just pointed to the chair in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.76,0:28:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,front of the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.97,0:28:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You already know why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.59,0:28:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.57,0:28:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas poured two coffees without
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.08,0:28:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.99,0:28:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm pretty sure I shouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.38,0:28:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,open my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.55,0:28:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena accepted the coffee and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.32,0:28:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.61,0:28:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.53,0:28:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Her voice came out firmer than
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.94,0:28:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,she expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.13,0:28:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your his friend, I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.05,0:28:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were also the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.28,0:28:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who looked me in the eye that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.47,0:28:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,night at the ball
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.17,0:28:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't pretend not to see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.60,0:28:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what you were seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.01,0:28:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to know who kit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.07,0:28:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas let the coffee rest
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.36,0:28:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,between his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.77,0:28:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He stared at the tabletop for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.00,0:28:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,long enough
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.47,0:28:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that Roeena understood the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.09,0:28:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,answer would hurt him too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.01,0:28:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit was his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.37,0:28:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it last.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.55,0:28:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.41,0:28:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Was.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.21,0:28:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they say in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.27,0:28:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.33,0:28:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.79,0:28:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas raised his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.33,0:28:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a new caution in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.03,0:28:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The caution of someone crossing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.73,0:28:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a line and knowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.11,0:28:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I say there was a boating
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.46,0:28:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,accident 10 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.59,0:28:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that the boat was found
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.91,0:28:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.03,0:28:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That the family buried a closed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.69,0:28:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,casket.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.59,0:29:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He paused.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.53,0:29:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And that Jego never believed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.37,0:29:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena felt her own chest drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.63,0:29:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he never believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.61,0:29:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas shook his head slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.57,0:29:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.41,0:29:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not today.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.31,0:29:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.33,0:29:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't mine to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.33,0:29:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.17,0:29:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already said more than I
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.46,0:29:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,should.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.23,0:29:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.39,0:29:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.87,0:29:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.07,0:29:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then come back here when he
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.35,0:29:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.07,0:29:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She got up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,At the door she stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.53,0:29:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't look back when she
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,said.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.53,0:29:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.49,0:29:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.93,0:29:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He kept looking at her coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.22,0:29:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that hadn't been drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.25,0:29:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time in 10
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.00,0:29:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.75,0:29:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he felt he might be betraying
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.14,0:29:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the right friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.37,0:29:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Back at the house near the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.46,0:29:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,river.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.23,0:29:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena found Neve in the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.38,0:29:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.29,0:29:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,arranging sprigs of basil in a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.08,0:29:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,glass jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.07,0:29:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The old housekeeper had her hair
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.72,0:29:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,pinned up in a loose bun
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.95,0:29:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and wore the same grey apron as
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.83,0:29:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,always.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.77,0:29:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena stopped in the doorway
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.21,0:29:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for a second before going in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.01,0:29:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve belonged to that house more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.95,0:29:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,than Jego belonged to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.59,0:29:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone knew, it was her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.97,0:29:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.77,0:29:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman looked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.65,0:30:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She smiled with that small smile
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.34,0:30:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,she kept for Roeena.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.95,0:30:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.17,0:30:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I make some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.67,0:30:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.41,0:30:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.39,0:30:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The smile disappeared so fast
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.96,0:30:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Roeena almost doubted it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.54,0:30:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,had existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.87,0:30:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve's hands gripped the jar too
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.55,0:30:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.33,0:30:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the sprigs slipped and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.57,0:30:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,fell into the sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.95,0:30:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.83,0:30:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.77,0:30:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve looked at the door leading
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.05,0:30:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.11,0:30:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the window that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.33,0:30:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,faced the garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.53,0:30:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where the morning Jasmine was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.91,0:30:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,still closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.89,0:30:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the counter as if
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.23,0:30:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer might be printed on
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.53,0:30:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the marble.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.01,0:30:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.95,0:30:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.19,0:30:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena took a step closer,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.99,0:30:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've been sleeping in this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.25,0:30:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,house for six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.59,0:30:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't pretend anymore that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.22,0:30:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.29,0:30:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He avoids the terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.99,0:30:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You avoid answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.55,0:30:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Udora has never said that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.25,0:30:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,name near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.37,0:30:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night I asked my
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.54,0:30:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.45,0:30:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the word slipped out before she
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.85,0:30:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,could choose another.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.13,0:30:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.79,0:30:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve closed her eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.51,0:30:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He avoids the terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.19,0:30:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The voice came out broken almost
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.74,0:30:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,inaudible,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.23,0:30:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's where the boat
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.92,0:31:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,set out that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.53,0:31:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena didn't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.85,0:31:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What night, Neve?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.97,0:31:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.07,0:31:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve wiped her hands on her
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.26,0:31:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,apron.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.89,0:31:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A mechanical gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.53,0:31:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The only night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.89,0:31:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The one this family could never
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.35,0:31:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bury properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.47,0:31:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned her face aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.17,0:31:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me for the rest dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.09,0:31:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.17,0:31:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena swallowed hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.67,0:31:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kitt.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.11,0:31:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Neve continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.47,0:31:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And now she was speaking to the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.06,0:31:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,basil, not to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.21,0:31:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At a way of laughing loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.81,0:31:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Udora used to say he'd wake
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.68,0:31:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.21,0:31:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,house when he was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.23,0:31:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A small smile crossed her face
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.64,0:31:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.77,0:31:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a beautiful laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.27,0:31:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Too full for that mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.87,0:31:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You have his laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.27,0:31:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena had to grip the counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.09,0:31:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The air went out of her slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.89,0:31:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hand pressed on the cold
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.51,0:31:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,marble.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.41,0:31:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The certainty assembling inside
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.05,0:31:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,her ribs like an old building
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.58,0:31:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,rising from the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.09,0:31:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose laugh it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.41,0:31:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the sentence came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.01,0:31:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why Udora had looked at her that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.86,0:31:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.33,0:31:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As she left that night at the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.88,0:31:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.59,0:31:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Neve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.87,0:31:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.11,0:31:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The housekeeper held her arm for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.94,0:31:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.83,0:32:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Her fingers were firm and dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.21,0:32:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He suffered.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.13,0:32:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let anger make you forget
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.65,0:32:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.09,0:32:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.41,0:32:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The weekend passed in a silence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.25,0:32:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.11,0:32:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego didn't try to enter the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.40,0:32:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.35,0:32:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena didn't come down from
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.57,0:32:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.43,0:32:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling carried trays in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.77,0:32:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.75,0:32:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Left them outside the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.39,0:32:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Collected them untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.15,0:32:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,On Saturday afternoon, Roeena
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.79,0:32:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote in her planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.39,0:32:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The list of everything she
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.58,0:32:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,needed to trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.85,0:32:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Payments.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.27,0:32:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Names.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.75,0:32:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.79,0:32:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.85,0:32:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She started with the public
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.17,0:32:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,library in downtown Savannah,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.58,0:32:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where the old newspapers were
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.99,0:32:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,kept on microfilm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.53,0:32:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She spent hours hunched over a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.19,0:32:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,reader that hummed softly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.09,0:32:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of dry paper and old
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.77,0:32:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,air conditioning filling the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.33,0:32:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,small room.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.31,0:32:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She found the headline she knew
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.82,0:32:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.73,0:32:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Quint Air Missing After Coastal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.44,0:32:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.29,0:32:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The photo was small, grainy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.55,0:32:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A young man smiling with his
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.09,0:32:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,mouth open.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.97,0:32:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,His teeth a little crooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.11,0:32:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,His hair touseled by the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.77,0:32:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked at the face for a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.14,0:32:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.03,0:32:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something of Jego in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.52,0:32:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.85,0:33:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the shape of the eyes in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.37,0:33:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,line of the jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.61,0:33:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There was also that Frank Lough,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.28,0:33:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Nieve, had described.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.91,0:33:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Too wide for a newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.32,0:33:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,portrait impossible to contain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.71,0:33:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,On Sunday, she cross-referenced
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.64,0:33:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.87,0:33:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked feeling for old
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.03,0:33:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,statements with some excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.91,0:33:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the assistant, who already
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.37,0:33:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,liked her more than he should,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.31,0:33:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,gave in without asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.61,0:33:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She found regular payments going
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.55,0:33:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out of a parallel account of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.25,0:33:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego's.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.87,0:33:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Monthly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Always the same rounded amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.77,0:33:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Always to the office of a lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.55,0:33:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with no recognizable family
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.05,0:33:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.67,0:33:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She found receipts from a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.01,0:33:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,pharmacy in a small town she'd
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.62,0:33:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,never heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.53,0:33:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She found, among the clippings,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.16,0:33:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nieve kept in an old envelope in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.84,0:33:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen cabinet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.47,0:33:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A photo, where a teenage kid
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.33,0:33:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared beside an older man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.69,0:33:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The same face she'd recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.17,0:33:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the more recent records.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.51,0:33:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo called it three in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.97,0:33:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,morning on Monday.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.45,0:33:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena answered on the second
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.71,0:33:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.47,0:33:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Roe, I had the strange feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.72,0:33:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that you needed to laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.37,0:33:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.27,0:33:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, I was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.31,0:33:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Woke up out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.55,0:33:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at the ceiling and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.44,0:33:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.25,0:34:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this woman needs to laugh right
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.20,0:34:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.81,0:34:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.91,0:34:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She laughed for real mouth open
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.51,0:34:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the silent
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.90,0:34:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.89,0:34:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she started to cry and kept
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.51,0:34:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,laughing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.41,0:34:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and Marlo on the other end
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.72,0:34:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stayed quiet,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.71,0:34:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for the hurricane to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.03,0:34:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.27,0:34:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out the name Roeena said
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.48,0:34:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when she was able.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.09,0:34:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid guy, he was his brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.45,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was, that's what Silas said.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.95,0:34:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo breathed in deep and do
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.58,0:34:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.63,0:34:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe nobody pays for a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.07,0:34:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,pharmacy for a dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.79,0:34:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas on the other end.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.99,0:34:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Roe, Marlo's voice was
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.03,0:34:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,serious now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.17,0:34:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you want to go down
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.62,0:34:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.51,0:34:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.73,0:34:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then hold on tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.11,0:34:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Roeena looked at the planner
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.25,0:34:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,open on the mattress,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.63,0:34:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and address had appeared twice
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.08,0:34:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the receipts.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.85,0:34:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A small town a few hours by
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.36,0:34:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,train from Savannah,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.07,0:34:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a name that matched the man from
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.49,0:34:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the old photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.57,0:34:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She circled everything in red
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.08,0:34:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,pen,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.67,0:34:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and underlined the address three
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.20,0:34:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,times,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.91,0:34:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the pressure of the pen leaving
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.33,0:34:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a groove on the paper below.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.11,0:34:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.81,0:35:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego was sitting in the study
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.07,0:35:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with a glass of whiskey he
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.19,0:35:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't touched in hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.67,0:35:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd heard the taxi arrive in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.89,0:35:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.81,0:35:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd heard the taxi leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.33,0:35:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd heard Roeena ask feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.65,0:35:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for the statements,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.11,0:35:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with an excuse he knew because
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.65,0:35:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,he himself was the one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.83,0:35:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who'd used that excuse decades
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.04,0:35:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.73,0:35:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew she was piecing it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.80,0:35:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,together.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.55,0:35:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew she was going to find
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.07,0:35:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.47,0:35:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the first time in 10
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.87,0:35:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,years,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.67,0:35:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't tell whether he was
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.87,0:35:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid of what she'd discover,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.55,0:35:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or afraid of what he'd feel when
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.19,0:35:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,she knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.01,0:35:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran his hand over his
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.14,0:35:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,forehead,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.05,0:35:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,his hand was trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.59,0:35:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the guest room, Roeena closed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.28,0:35:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the planner,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.51,0:35:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a name, an address, a small
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.97,0:35:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,town,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.79,0:35:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that had come before.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.59,0:35:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The old story, the charade at
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.90,0:35:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the ball, the coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.85,0:35:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,without a recorder, had been
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.34,0:35:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,training for this decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.49,0:35:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned off the light, and in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.14,0:35:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.83,0:35:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she heard clearly the sound the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.43,0:35:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,empty chair made inside her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.43,0:35:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was no longer a creek, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.49,0:35:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole name.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.09,0:35:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 4, The Town With No
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.85,0:35:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Name.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.55,0:35:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In a scaven on Tuesday morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.49,0:36:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and he gave in because Roeena
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.89,0:36:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.09,0:36:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She walked into his office
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.19,0:36:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,without knocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.37,0:36:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She placed the open planner on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.88,0:36:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,his desk,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.77,0:36:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the address circled in red,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.17,0:36:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of the man from the old
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.27,0:36:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,photo written beside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.15,0:36:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.41,0:36:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas read it, leaned back
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.65,0:36:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,against the chair and closed his
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.17,0:36:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.43,0:36:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,like someone who knew this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.69,0:36:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,moment would come sooner or
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.00,0:36:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,later,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.63,0:36:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and had chosen too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.39,0:36:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to this on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.93,0:36:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I get to almost everything on my
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.55,0:36:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,own, Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.65,0:36:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The open his eyes, there was
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.01,0:36:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt in them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.19,0:36:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,An old guilty no longer tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.86,0:36:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,disguise beneath the efficiency
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.47,0:36:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the faithful assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.33,0:36:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If I complete the picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.89,0:36:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago will kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.95,0:36:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago is already dying inside
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.11,0:36:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.07,0:36:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.05,0:36:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.09,0:36:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To bury both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.69,0:36:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas kept looking at her for a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.10,0:36:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,length of time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.73,0:36:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that seemed to stretch beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.51,0:36:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,how long Silas usually lasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.71,0:36:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he opened a desk drawer,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.47,0:36:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and took out a small card no
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.92,0:36:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,letterhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.89,0:36:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,with a name written by hand on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.54,0:36:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,one side,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.41,0:36:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and an address on the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.99,0:37:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He slid it across the desk with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.48,0:37:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,two fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.61,0:37:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,like someone handing something
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.03,0:37:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,over,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.27,0:37:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time apologizing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.17,0:37:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for having taken so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.07,0:37:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who carries the money is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.63,0:37:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.31,0:37:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,His voice came out low, almost
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.23,0:37:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.07,0:37:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives between Savannah and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.41,0:37:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.19,0:37:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes the trip by train once
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.75,0:37:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a month,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.57,0:37:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,always on the first Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.17,0:37:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He tapped the card lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.95,0:37:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid lives in that town under
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.29,0:37:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,another name.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.35,0:37:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to tell you which.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.99,0:37:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That he'll have to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.19,0:37:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.15,0:37:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna took the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.41,0:37:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She felt the paper way more than
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.81,0:37:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it should,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.65,0:37:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,more than any paper card should
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.41,0:37:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,weigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.17,0:37:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.49,0:37:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna, Silas leaned forward his
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.38,0:37:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,elbows on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.93,0:37:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't want to come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.37,0:37:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,don't force it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.19,0:37:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He has that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.37,0:37:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't force it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.79,0:37:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And please, his voice nearly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.26,0:37:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,broke before reaching the end of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.93,0:37:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.13,0:37:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of Jago when you come
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.85,0:37:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.49,0:37:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She tucked the card into the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.90,0:37:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,inside pocket of her bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.49,0:37:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She stood up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.47,0:37:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She was almost at the door when
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.90,0:37:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he spoke again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.17,0:37:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.89,0:37:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,By now, why did you tell me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.31,0:38:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He took a while to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.51,0:38:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When he answered, he looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.37,0:38:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.45,0:38:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.57,0:38:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the street below where
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.63,0:38:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah went on a head,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.79,0:38:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.83,0:38:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I watched Jago spend 10
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.80,0:38:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,years dying slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.45,0:38:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and I watched you arrive and him
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.14,0:38:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,start to live again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.51,0:38:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't watch him lose you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.94,0:38:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking he's protecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.51,0:38:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned his gaze back to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.31,0:38:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone needs to break this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.59,0:38:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.29,0:38:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one with the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.61,0:38:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,courage to break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.81,0:38:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna nodded once.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.39,0:38:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She left.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.57,0:38:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside Savannah's air had that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.37,0:38:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,humid mid-afternoon heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.83,0:38:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dense and green, with the smell
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.90,0:38:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of wet earth mixed with the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.70,0:38:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,distant salt of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.97,0:38:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,estuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.83,0:38:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She walked to the station
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.98,0:38:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,without hurry,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.15,0:38:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling the uneven paving under
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.65,0:38:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,her shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.75,0:38:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The sounds of the city around
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.17,0:38:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.55,0:38:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The street car passing by, a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.19,0:38:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,child shouting in some backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.59,0:38:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The clinking of glasses in a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.99,0:38:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,corner cafe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.15,0:38:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She bought a one-way ticket for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.41,0:38:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the four-ocluck train,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.81,0:38:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and called Marlo from the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.94,0:38:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,payphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.81,0:38:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.87,0:38:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.73,0:38:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.71,0:38:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo paused for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.47,0:39:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind that contains questions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.40,0:39:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,one decides not to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.19,0:39:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to call someone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.87,0:39:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't come back in 24
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.43,0:39:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.15,0:39:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.37,0:39:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.15,0:39:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Before boarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.41,0:39:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna stopped at the house near
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.71,0:39:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.55,0:39:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She came in through the side
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.74,0:39:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,door.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.33,0:39:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Went up to the guest room
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.38,0:39:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through some clothes into a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.52,0:39:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,small suitcase,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.87,0:39:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with the objectivity of someone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.50,0:39:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows that thinking too much
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.19,0:39:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is a luxury that doesn't fit in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.89,0:39:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.07,0:39:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She went down to the kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.44,0:39:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where the afternoon light came
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.86,0:39:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in slanted through the shutters,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.37,0:39:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and drew thin stripes across the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.41,0:39:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,stone floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.57,0:39:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrote a short letter on a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.91,0:39:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,piece of writing paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.43,0:39:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter had a single line.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.17,0:39:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come back when I bring what
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.50,0:39:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't bring on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.03,0:39:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She left the letter on top of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.24,0:39:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the day's newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.55,0:39:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She left.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.61,0:39:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline saw her come down the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.86,0:39:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,stairs with the suitcase,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.51,0:39:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.79,0:39:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked him to call a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.73,0:39:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He called one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.89,0:39:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the taxi door closed,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.63,0:39:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the assistant said quietly
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.95,0:39:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,almost to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.29,0:39:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have a good trip miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.71,0:39:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't correct him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.81,0:39:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The train left Savannah at four
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.75,0:39:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,o'clock sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.21,0:40:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Roenachosa seat by the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.23,0:40:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and rested her forehead against
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.74,0:40:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the cold glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.93,0:40:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and for a long time thought
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.10,0:40:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,about nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.15,0:40:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She passed low houses, flooded
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.14,0:40:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.21,0:40:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a small town with a rusty water
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.75,0:40:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,tower in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.35,0:40:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a river that wasn't the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.24,0:40:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.19,0:40:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a line of Cyprus's cutting into
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.77,0:40:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the copper-coloured sky of the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.30,0:40:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,late afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.71,0:40:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun began to set slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.93,0:40:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,tinting the landscape and orange
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.35,0:40:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that looked like a painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.59,0:40:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She opened the planner and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.03,0:40:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,re-read the address three times
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.75,0:40:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as if she could forget it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.63,0:40:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and she knew she couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.35,0:40:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side at the house
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.60,0:40:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,near the river,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.81,0:40:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager arrived at seven at night
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.49,0:40:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and felt that something was
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.74,0:40:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,missing before he looked in any
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.19,0:40:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.15,0:40:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if the house had
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.37,0:40:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,changed weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.45,0:40:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not temperature, not sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.69,0:40:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.79,0:40:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He passed through the living
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.93,0:40:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,room the kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.11,0:40:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,saw the letter on top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.27,0:40:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.27,0:40:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.27,0:40:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He read it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.25,0:40:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and something in him collapsed
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.03,0:40:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same silent precision
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.82,0:40:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of a structure
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.65,0:40:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives way from within,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.95,0:40:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with no visible warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.79,0:41:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the same old night
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.06,0:41:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,returning to his nostrils,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.95,0:41:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the smell of the sea after the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.32,0:41:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.11,0:41:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the taste of metal in his mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.05,0:41:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical animal certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.53,0:41:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had lost again,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.07,0:41:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and that this time the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.09,0:41:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,punishment was proportional to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.49,0:41:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.09,0:41:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He let the letter drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.53,0:41:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat on the kitchen floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.33,0:41:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He truly sat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.41,0:41:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,His back against the door of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.88,0:41:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,low cabinet
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.39,0:41:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and his hands open on his knees
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.43,0:41:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he didn't know what to do
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.06,0:41:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.89,0:41:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He stayed there too long for it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.21,0:41:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to be dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.25,0:41:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Scyl is showed up half an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.62,0:41:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,later.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.31,0:41:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He hadn't been called, he simply
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.02,0:41:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.63,0:41:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He came in through the side
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.88,0:41:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,door,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.49,0:41:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,found Jager on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.79,0:41:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,knelt beside him without
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.86,0:41:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.99,0:41:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.19,0:41:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager raised his face slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.37,0:41:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something in his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.83,0:41:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.13,0:41:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an exhaustion so deep,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.01,0:41:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it passed beneath the anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.85,0:41:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and reached a place the anger no
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.40,0:41:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,longer reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.13,0:41:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You told her what,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.89,0:41:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the name,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.91,0:41:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the address,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.05,0:41:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the man who carries the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.25,0:41:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager closed his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.79,0:41:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It took him a full second to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.08,0:41:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.15,0:41:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hit you siless.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.93,0:42:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.83,0:42:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager didn't hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.25,0:42:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He clenched his fist, raised it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.77,0:42:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fist stopped in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.13,0:42:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,before touching anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.67,0:42:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He lowered his hands slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.51,0:42:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,rested it on his knee,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.89,0:42:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and stared at his own fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.71,0:42:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he didn't recognize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.55,0:42:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As if that man sitting on the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.90,0:42:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,floor of his kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.83,0:42:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,belonged to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.13,0:42:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She went alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.83,0:42:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She did,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.79,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and if he doesn't take her in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.53,0:42:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll take her in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.77,0:42:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't say no to anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.10,0:42:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.91,0:42:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He never could.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.13,0:42:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager swallowed twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.75,0:42:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he takes her in and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.99,0:42:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.39,0:42:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.81,0:42:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.37,0:42:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jager squeezed his eyes shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.57,0:42:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside something in him was
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.89,0:42:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reconstructing the timeline
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with a precision that hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.45,0:42:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The train's schedule,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.75,0:42:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.75,0:42:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the time she'd need to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.65,0:42:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The night she'd spend alone in a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.10,0:42:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,town he knew
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.65,0:42:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from a map and from receipts,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.57,0:42:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but never with his own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.47,0:42:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.57,0:42:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never allowed himself to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.02,0:42:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,go,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.39,0:42:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and now she was going for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.11,0:42:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With the courage he'd traded for
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.66,0:42:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,control,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.53,0:42:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was sitting on the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.50,0:42:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen floor
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.01,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because he no longer knew what
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with his own body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.25,0:43:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.19,0:43:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.97,0:43:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If she comes back,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.31,0:43:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.43,0:43:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.61,0:43:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If she comes back.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.15,0:43:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas rested his hand on his
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.42,0:43:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,shoulder and left it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.85,0:43:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll come back, Jager.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.21,0:43:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the small town, the train
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.81,0:43:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived at 9.20 at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.23,0:43:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Roina got off with the small
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.88,0:43:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,suitcase,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.93,0:43:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the asphalt different under
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.38,0:43:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,her feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.47,0:43:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,quieter without savanna's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.63,0:43:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,constant noise,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.81,0:43:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and looked for a small hotel a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.18,0:43:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,block from the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.71,0:43:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with painted wooden windows and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.69,0:43:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a ceiling fan that turned
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.28,0:43:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.19,0:43:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She paid for one night,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.79,0:43:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,went up, didn't have dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.83,0:43:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She sat on the edge of the bed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.22,0:43:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,until dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.11,0:43:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with Silas's card in her hand
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.61,0:43:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and the address memorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.51,0:43:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning, she followed the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.27,0:43:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,map on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.39,0:43:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The town was smaller than she'd
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.65,0:43:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,expected,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.01,0:43:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a main street with five shops,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.59,0:43:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a central square with a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.78,0:43:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,bandstand painted white and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.17,0:43:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,peeling at the edges,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.69,0:43:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,low houses scattered along dirt
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.26,0:43:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,roads where grass grew down the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.83,0:43:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.57,0:43:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The address led her to a modest
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.26,0:43:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,light blue house,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.53,0:43:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with an neglected front garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.43,0:44:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and a rocking chair sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.72,0:44:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,motionless on the porch.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.35,0:44:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She knocked on the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.89,0:44:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,once with her knuckle, firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.99,0:44:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A man opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.39,0:44:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She recognized him before she
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.72,0:44:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,looked properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.91,0:44:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She recognized him by the shape
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.41,0:44:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.99,0:44:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by the line of the jaw,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.03,0:44:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way he stood in the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.21,0:44:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.19,0:44:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The same way Jago had a filling
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.78,0:44:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a threshold
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.35,0:44:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that presence that filled the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.14,0:44:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,space even in silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.15,0:44:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Except, this man was thinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.34,0:44:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,harder,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.37,0:44:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with a small scar crossing his
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.06,0:44:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,left eyebrow and lighter hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.01,0:44:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sun bleached.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.19,0:44:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the slightly crooked
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.41,0:44:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,teeth she remembered from the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.73,0:44:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,newspaper photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.03,0:44:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit, he was paralyzed for a full
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.25,0:44:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,second,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.15,0:44:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then he stepped back half a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.43,0:44:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,step,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.67,0:44:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.41,0:44:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena Pike, she didn't move
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.95,0:44:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.83,0:44:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been with your brother for
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.10,0:44:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.91,0:44:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The silence that came after was
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.30,0:44:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,dense and loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.69,0:44:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit rested one hand on the door
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.13,0:44:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,frame,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.75,0:44:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he needed the support,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.55,0:44:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,his fingers gripping the painted
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.16,0:44:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.81,0:44:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.11,0:44:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.03,0:44:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He sent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.03,0:44:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't even know I came.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.07,0:45:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit looked at her for a long
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.24,0:45:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.79,0:45:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The physical shock was still in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.40,0:45:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,him,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.83,0:45:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the old anger rose
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.78,0:45:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.03,0:45:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fear hidden beneath the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.71,0:45:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,anger too,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.25,0:45:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was something else,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.37,0:45:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper, that he could no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.02,0:45:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,name well.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.87,0:45:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he stepped aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.43,0:45:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.37,0:45:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The living room was small and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.88,0:45:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,clean,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.71,0:45:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with that silence of a place
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.97,0:45:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,where a person has lived alone
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.32,0:45:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.33,0:45:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a dark wooden table,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.05,0:45:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,two chairs, a sofa with warm
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.92,0:45:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,fabric on the backrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.89,0:45:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a shelf with few books and no
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.62,0:45:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,ornaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.87,0:45:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit pointed to one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.09,0:45:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.95,0:45:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena sat, he stayed standing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.77,0:45:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,leaning against the wall arms
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.53,0:45:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,crossed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.01,0:45:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.17,0:45:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.19,0:45:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.95,0:45:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,without embellishing, without
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.24,0:45:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.99,0:45:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked about the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.04,0:45:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,investigators Jago had hired
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.50,0:45:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.71,0:45:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,About the money he left with
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.18,0:45:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,lawyers who had no names,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.03,0:45:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about the medications paid for
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.63,0:45:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by third parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.89,0:45:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The debts settled before they
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.34,0:45:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,became dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.77,0:45:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,About the empty chair no one
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.09,0:45:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,explained and no one removed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.42,0:45:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.63,0:45:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked about Yudora,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.27,0:46:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,about the way she never said his
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.77,0:46:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.47,0:46:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,About the way once on the porch
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.04,0:46:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,she had murmured about a lost
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.51,0:46:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.81,0:46:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked about the terrace
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.45,0:46:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jago avoided.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.71,0:46:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked about the envelope
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.04,0:46:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.07,0:46:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,About the control he confused
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.72,0:46:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.71,0:46:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,About the old fear he carried
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.11,0:46:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because he thought that if he
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.51,0:46:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.15,0:46:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd lose everything again.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.91,0:46:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit listened without
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.78,0:46:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.99,0:46:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When she finished, he stayed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.48,0:46:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,silent for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.81,0:46:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.05,0:46:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A short, dry laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.05,0:46:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost a grunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.25,0:46:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent 10 years looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.83,0:46:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.21,0:46:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.15,0:46:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Without stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.35,0:46:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Without stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.57,0:46:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And he never came himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.83,0:46:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena hesitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.65,0:46:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought you didn't want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.02,0:46:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,found by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.83,0:46:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit closed his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.33,0:46:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside something that had been
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.98,0:46:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hard for 10 years began to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.40,0:46:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.23,0:46:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow and inevitable as a crack
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.83,0:46:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.91,0:46:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He swallowed once.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.09,0:46:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,swallowed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.23,0:46:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.35,0:46:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He was.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.51,0:46:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena's voice came out lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.23,0:46:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He just didn't know he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.97,0:46:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit peeled himself off the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.01,0:46:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He went to the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.45,0:47:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at the neglected garden
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.93,0:47:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long time at the grass
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.24,0:47:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,growing between the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.81,0:47:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cowl-mate coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.97,0:47:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They spent the afternoon and the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.32,0:47:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,night talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.39,0:47:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,On the porch with cups that went
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.81,0:47:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,cold twice in the sound of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.97,0:47:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,crickets filling the dark around
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.39,0:47:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,them, Kit spoke aloud for the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.96,0:47:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,first time about what he felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.03,0:47:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he'd fled because he
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.25,0:47:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thought he wasn't important to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.56,0:47:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.35,0:47:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But on that night, he'd asked
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.72,0:47:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,his brother for help and his
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.04,0:47:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,brother hadn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.51,0:47:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And he understood, in that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.81,0:47:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,instant, that his world was
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.17,0:47:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,worth less than a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.87,0:47:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That when the boat began to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.25,0:47:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,crack in the storm, he had two
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.78,0:47:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds to choose between
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.06,0:47:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.47,0:47:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or sinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.63,0:47:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he chose to swim because the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.98,0:47:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anger was greater than the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.08,0:47:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.19,0:47:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That when he came out the other
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.70,0:47:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,side, on a stretch of beach he
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.15,0:47:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't even know where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.03,0:47:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He made the decision to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.02,0:47:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear because he thought no
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.36,0:47:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,one would miss him enough to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.57,0:47:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,really
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.83,0:47:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,look.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.61,0:47:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And he looked, Kit said, looking
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.42,0:47:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bandstand in the square
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.11,0:47:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.61,0:47:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.21,0:47:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.89,0:47:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit ran his hand over his eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.50,0:47:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.39,0:47:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He made a mistake out of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.05,0:47:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.27,0:48:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not out of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.93,0:48:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Browiness spoke low, looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.64,0:48:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the same point he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.19,0:48:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's afraid of you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.07,0:48:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Of what happened, and of what he
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.85,0:48:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.81,0:48:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit laughed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.13,0:48:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This time without the dryness of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.85,0:48:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,before, almost with affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.07,0:48:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And affection he clearly hadn't
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.65,0:48:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,expected to feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.93,0:48:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk about him as if you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.85,0:48:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,knew him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.75,0:48:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.85,0:48:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.85,0:48:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.11,0:48:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.45,0:48:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They stayed silent for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.81,0:48:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,With the warm wind passing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.22,0:48:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,through the branches of the old
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.90,0:48:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnolia,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.93,0:48:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,growing in the corner of the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.13,0:48:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.03,0:48:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,then Kit spoke, looking at his
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.92,0:48:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.05,0:48:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If I come back, I come back
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.72,0:48:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,once.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.53,0:48:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.73,0:48:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't work, I leave
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.35,0:48:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.17,0:48:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time no one finds me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.39,0:48:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.25,0:48:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know if I'll be able
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.71,0:48:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.65,0:48:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to know that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.55,0:48:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit nodded slowly, like someone
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.28,0:48:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,making a deal with himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.13,0:48:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as much as with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.11,0:48:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning he took a small
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.56,0:48:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.75,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.93,0:48:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina looked at that suitcase
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.29,0:48:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and understood the size of what
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.69,0:49:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he carried.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.73,0:49:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in what was inside, but in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.52,0:49:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,how little there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.25,0:49:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Before they left for the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.49,0:49:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,station, she sent a single
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.83,0:49:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,message to Silas,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.11,0:49:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from the telegraph on the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.25,0:49:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.01,0:49:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We arrived tomorrow, prepare you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.79,0:49:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.55,0:49:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,While they waited for the train
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.98,0:49:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on the wooden bench of the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.18,0:49:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,town's only platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.79,0:49:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit looked at the horizon and
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.53,0:49:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,said,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.83,0:49:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,without turning his face,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.40,0:49:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.15,0:49:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,if you brought me here for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.87,0:49:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he swallowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.17,0:49:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, she didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.25,0:49:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She simply rested her hand over
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.16,0:49:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,his hand, and his hand was cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.65,0:49:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and hers was too.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.31,0:49:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The train whistled in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.59,0:49:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 5, 10 years in a single
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.81,0:49:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,room.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.45,0:49:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.37,0:49:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego didn't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.91,0:49:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The house near the Savannah
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.27,0:49:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,River was so silent
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.23,0:49:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that he could hear his own pulse
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.93,0:49:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in his throat,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.67,0:49:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on the study floor
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.93,0:49:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,leaning against the shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.59,0:49:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,his suit rumpled and his tie
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.12,0:49:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,loose since the small hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.95,0:49:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He counted time by the way the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.21,0:49:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,light came through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.99,0:49:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First blue, then gray, then a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.79,0:50:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,timid goal that arrived to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.40,0:50:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,insulting for the weight of the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.32,0:50:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.99,0:50:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowina's letter was still folded
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.55,0:50:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in his lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.45,0:50:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He no longer needed to reread it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.88,0:50:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what was written.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.47,0:50:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come back when I bring what
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.93,0:50:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't bring on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.51,0:50:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Each word weighed more than the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.15,0:50:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,last.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.83,0:50:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Each word opened a door he'd
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.26,0:50:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,kept closed for 10 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.53,0:50:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and pushed him inside it with no
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.21,0:50:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,choice, no warning,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.79,0:50:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,without even letting him breathe
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.22,0:50:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,first.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.95,0:50:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside, Jego had the cold
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.46,0:50:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,certainty that the punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.22,0:50:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,had finally arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.93,0:50:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the form of scandal, not
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.65,0:50:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.23,0:50:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the form of a headline,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.83,0:50:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of a woman with an
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.43,0:50:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,ink scar in the Sunday paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.31,0:50:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,going after what he hadn't had
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.62,0:50:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to bring.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.91,0:50:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the most cowardly part of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.74,0:50:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,him,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.15,0:50:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a low voice said that this scar
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.62,0:50:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,could open again,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.85,0:50:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that this time the woman too
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.18,0:50:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,might not come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.13,0:50:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas came in at seven without
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.87,0:50:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,knocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.85,0:50:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought coffee Jego hadn't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.29,0:50:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,asked for,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.99,0:50:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and a silenced Jego didn't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.13,0:50:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood in the door frame
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.29,0:50:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting with that lawyer's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.44,0:50:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,patience of someone who'd
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.56,0:50:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,already seen too many
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.49,0:50:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,clients on the floor of his own
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.84,0:50:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,office.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.71,0:51:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk, Jego said without looking
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.66,0:51:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.01,0:51:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She arrived, she's with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.93,0:51:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.99,0:51:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She sent me a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.53,0:51:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Short, Silas hesitated, and at
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.26,0:51:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom of that hesitation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.93,0:51:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there was an old guilt the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.43,0:51:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,lawyer had
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.01,0:51:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to carry in silence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.64,0:51:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.53,0:51:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He held out the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.55,0:51:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego read the line on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.55,0:51:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and took a full second to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.11,0:51:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.61,0:51:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We arrived tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.25,0:51:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare you dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.63,0:51:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He closed his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.13,0:51:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt the room spin as if
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.43,0:51:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,someone had flipped the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.29,0:51:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a man inside him who
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.69,0:51:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to yell at Silas for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.95,0:51:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,giving up the thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.43,0:51:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There was another deeper who
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.95,0:51:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to kneel and give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.17,0:51:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one for half a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.47,0:51:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego stood up, grabbed Silas by
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.27,0:51:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the lapel, and stopped his fist
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.08,0:51:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the air before it closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.71,0:51:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,His hand trembled, it never
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.45,0:51:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,trembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.57,0:51:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hit, Silas said very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.97,0:51:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not a man who hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.69,0:51:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a man of anything right
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.22,0:51:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now, Jego answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.67,0:51:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And let go of the lapel like
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.08,0:51:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,someone releasing a rope too hot
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.69,0:51:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.55,0:51:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They stood still.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.83,0:51:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside a bird insisted on a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.47,0:52:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,whistle of three repeated notes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.29,0:52:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,without tiring, without mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.65,0:52:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego looked at his own
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,reflection in the glass of the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.98,0:52:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,picture frame,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.07,0:52:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and recognized neither the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.71,0:52:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,disheveled hair, nor the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.23,0:52:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,civilised despair his eyes held.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.25,0:52:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare her, he asked, and his
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.45,0:52:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,voice didn't quite obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.71,0:52:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.87,0:52:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.89,0:52:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.79,0:52:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego swallowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.05,0:52:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.03,0:52:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Silas looked at him long.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.65,0:52:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.93,0:52:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He left.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.77,0:52:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was feeling who arrived first
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.19,0:52:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at the quint mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.81,0:52:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Udora was having tea in the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.16,0:52:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,small parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.09,0:52:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The newspaper still untouched on
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.68,0:52:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the white linen napkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.31,0:52:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The matriarch looked up and
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.59,0:52:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,read.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.17,0:52:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the younger systems posture,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.80,0:52:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that something was coming before
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.48,0:52:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.01,0:52:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.73,0:52:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She waited, with that old skill
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.63,0:52:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of letting Silas do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.83,0:52:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs Rowena asked that you come
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.85,0:52:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to the main hall at five.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.79,0:52:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline said, with the trained
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.21,0:52:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,delicacy of someone delivering
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.68,0:52:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,news he didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.55,0:52:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Mr. Jego as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.47,0:52:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Udora folded the newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.92,0:52:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,carefully as if it might break.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.99,0:53:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hand, when it rested on the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.53,0:53:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,table, had a strange lightness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.02,0:53:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for the weight of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.69,0:53:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.59,0:53:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.87,0:53:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.83,0:53:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The matriarch didn't smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.31,0:53:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.17,0:53:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She nodded once and turned her
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.80,0:53:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,gaze to the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.33,0:53:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the garden trees swayed in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.84,0:53:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a breeze no one inside could
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.15,0:53:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.83,0:53:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The trainer arrived at four.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.67,0:53:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena got off on the savanna
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.11,0:53:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,platform with the same small bag
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.70,0:53:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd left with.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.79,0:53:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And a thin man beside her who
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.41,0:53:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,insisted on keeping three steps
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.14,0:53:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.33,0:53:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Like someone still deciding
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.83,0:53:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to stay, or turn around
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.54,0:53:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and disappear again.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.11,0:53:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt had his head down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.59,0:53:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,His cap pulled low.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.13,0:53:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,His backpack held tight against
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.63,0:53:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,his chest like a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.79,0:53:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Every sudden noise in the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.27,0:53:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,station made his jaw clench.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.27,0:53:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He stopped twice on the way to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.67,0:53:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.57,0:53:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And both times Rowena pretended
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.49,0:53:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,not to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.85,0:53:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing to walk at a pace
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.03,0:53:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that demanded nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.49,0:53:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.53,0:53:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, at the third stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.12,0:53:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,without pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.61,0:53:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to go back now, we
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.28,0:53:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.99,0:53:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you back and won't
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.19,0:53:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,tell anyone you set foot in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.35,0:53:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,savanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.21,0:54:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt swallowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.29,0:54:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.43,0:54:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what then.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.57,0:54:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that I forgot what the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.87,0:54:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,smell is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.05,0:54:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena looked at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.01,0:54:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an 18-year-old boy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.75,0:54:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,inside that thin man,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.39,0:54:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the boy was blinking hard
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.92,0:54:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not to cry on the sidewalk of a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.56,0:54:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,station full of strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.47,0:54:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't touch his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.91,0:54:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She just stood there at the same
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.22,0:54:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,height waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.33,0:54:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell is the same, she
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.59,0:54:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.69,0:54:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnolia and old money.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.65,0:54:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.73,0:54:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A quick laugh, almost a sob.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.03,0:54:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.81,0:54:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.11,0:54:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They got into the taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.75,0:54:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena told the driver to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.44,0:54:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.43,0:54:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 6 The Chair with Anona.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.43,0:54:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.75,0:54:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at the house near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.55,0:54:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt raised his face when the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.81,0:54:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,facade appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.03,0:54:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That heavy iron gate he knew
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.42,0:54:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,better than any other place in
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.91,0:54:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.79,0:54:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He stared at it for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.99,0:54:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A leaf came loose from one of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.52,0:54:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the tall trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.81,0:54:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and fell on the hood of the car
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.13,0:54:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lightness that seemed
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.32,0:54:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,calculated.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.51,0:54:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No one said anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.87,0:54:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.37,0:54:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt said, low.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.47,0:54:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make it to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.09,0:55:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,After that we decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.59,0:55:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they hate me, they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.48,0:55:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.03,0:55:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know how to hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.05,0:55:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.25,0:55:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The open the car door and got
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.57,0:55:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,out slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.51,0:55:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Like someone stepping onto a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.78,0:55:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,floor that might not hold his
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.09,0:55:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.87,0:55:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The main hall smelled of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.28,0:55:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnolia and old money.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.07,0:55:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The afternoon came in through
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.48,0:55:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the tall windows in bands of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.84,0:55:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,golden light,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.79,0:55:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that crossed the marble and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.89,0:55:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped at the empty chair near
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.16,0:55:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.03,0:55:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as if they knew exactly where to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.60,0:55:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,land.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.37,0:55:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena went in first.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.07,0:55:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She deliberately chose that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.53,0:55:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.29,0:55:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the living room, not the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.64,0:55:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,library, not J. Go's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.95,0:55:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Where everything had begun to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.63,0:55:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.73,0:55:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.81,0:55:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The same room where one night,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.34,0:55:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,month earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.67,0:55:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a woman in a borrowed dress had
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.39,0:55:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,held the face of a silent man
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.99,0:55:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and kissed him in front of 300
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.00,0:55:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.87,0:55:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.45,0:55:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The light came in at the same
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.94,0:55:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.83,0:55:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The chair was still empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.69,0:55:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Rowena positioned herself
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.88,0:55:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly where she had stood on
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.32,0:55:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.47,0:55:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As if she were marking a fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.92,0:55:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,point on a map,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.15,0:55:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,only she knew how to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.07,0:56:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitt stayed one step behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.57,0:56:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,still in his cap, still with his
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.42,0:56:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,hand closed around the strap of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.22,0:56:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.53,0:56:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline opened the double doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.49,0:56:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yudora came in first.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.05,0:56:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The matriarch noticed Rowena,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.13,0:56:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed the figure behind her.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.93,0:56:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And for a moment, tiny, almost
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.79,0:56:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.05,0:56:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,her spine seemed to give way a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.48,0:56:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,millimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.63,0:56:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She restrained it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.83,0:56:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept her chin high.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.37,0:56:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She crossed the hall to the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.62,0:56:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,center and stopped, waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.53,0:56:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go came in after, and his
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.39,0:56:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,world stopped turning.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.85,0:56:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a thin man in the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.81,0:56:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.63,0:56:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, with his cap pulled low, a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.96,0:56:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,small scar on his eyebrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.33,0:56:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,his shoulders narrower than
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.83,0:56:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,memory had drawn them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.29,0:56:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A man who slowly lowered the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.04,0:56:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cap,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.67,0:56:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,revealing his short hair, and
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.54,0:56:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,looked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.37,0:56:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was the gaze of the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.81,0:56:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,18-year-old boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.05,0:56:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who had taken a boat out alone
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.69,0:56:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on a stormy night,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.93,0:56:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,ten years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.45,0:56:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go said nothing for a length
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.85,0:56:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of time, no one there could
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.07,0:56:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.89,0:56:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He took a step than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.65,0:56:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.27,0:56:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside it was as if a dam had
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.46,0:56:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,given way.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.61,0:57:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The old guilt, the anguish of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.15,0:57:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the last two days,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.63,0:57:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of losing Rowena, all
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.32,0:57:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mixing into a single hot point
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.01,0:57:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of his chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.89,0:57:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,too hot to be born with
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.19,0:57:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,composure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.11,0:57:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt his throat tightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.73,0:57:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt his hands go cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.75,0:57:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt with brutal clarity that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.30,0:57:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the punishment hadn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.97,0:57:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That life, against any
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.31,0:57:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,deserving, had given something
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.14,0:57:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,back.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.81,0:57:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.21,0:57:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And his voice came out choked,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.69,0:57:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.23,0:57:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The voice of a big boy that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.11,0:57:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't fit that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.97,0:57:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit, Kit dropped the backpack on
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.78,0:57:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.79,0:57:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The thud was dry on the marble.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.99,0:57:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran away, he said, and his
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.87,0:57:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,mouth trembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.35,0:57:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran away because I thought I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.82,0:57:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't important to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.65,0:57:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go closed his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.49,0:57:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A tear fell before he could
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.91,0:57:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,command his body to hold it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.33,0:57:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,back.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.91,0:57:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then another. He didn't wipe
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.64,0:57:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.19,0:57:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent ten years, he answered,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.14,0:57:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to fix the worst choice
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.02,0:57:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.71,0:57:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit shook his head incredulous,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.56,0:57:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the shaking became a tremor,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.89,0:57:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tremor became a short
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.69,0:57:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,dry sob.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.75,0:58:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go crossed the rest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.13,0:58:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hall in three strides,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.51,0:58:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and hugged his brother any which
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.36,0:58:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.07,0:58:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A crooked hug without elegance,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.37,0:58:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,without the composure all of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.89,0:58:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.93,0:58:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A hug that had waited ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.62,0:58:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.59,0:58:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that now happened all at
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.28,0:58:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,once, clumsy, and urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.43,0:58:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit was slow to return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.23,0:58:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When he did, he gripped J. Go's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.28,0:58:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,coat,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.61,0:58:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he were holding on so as
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.35,0:58:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,not to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.49,0:58:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go's coat at the back had
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.54,0:58:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.77,0:58:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The feared matriarch, the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.33,0:58:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who demanded proof of love in
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.79,0:58:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the middle of a crowded hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.71,0:58:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman Roena had met with
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.35,0:58:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes of steel, took a step
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.88,0:58:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.87,0:58:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then another. And with no
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.48,0:58:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,audience, without elegance,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.63,0:58:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,without any of the posture all
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.24,0:58:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of Savannah knew by heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.01,0:58:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,J. Go's coat on the marble floor
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.00,0:58:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,beside her lost son.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.53,0:58:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The tweed dress folded like an
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.21,0:58:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,old cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.77,0:58:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A hand sought Kit's face without
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.70,0:58:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to touch it right
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.45,0:58:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.05,0:58:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy, she said, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.49,0:58:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,knife-edged voice became a voice
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.32,0:58:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with no edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.57,0:58:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy, Kit turned to his mother
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.44,0:58:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and couldn't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.97,0:59:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He just rested his forehead on
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.31,0:59:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,her shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.49,0:59:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Udora closed her arms around her
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.45,0:59:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,son with a care no one ever had
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.34,0:59:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,seen that woman show.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.07,0:59:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena watched from the doorway,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.11,0:59:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,inside she felt her body way
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.59,0:59:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from two sides at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.17,0:59:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There was relief, yes, the real,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.35,0:59:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,physical relief
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.37,0:59:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeing the family finally
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.01,0:59:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,occupy the space it needed to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.72,0:59:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,occupy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.69,0:59:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was an exhaustion she
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.04,0:59:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't noticed accumulate,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.83,0:59:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until the adrenaline dropped for
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.67,0:59:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,good. The last 48 hours had
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.23,0:59:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,taken everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.67,0:59:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was two something hard
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.49,0:59:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of her chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.45,0:59:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,something that made her
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.50,0:59:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.73,0:59:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,belonged to those three and that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.42,0:59:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn't need to sign it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.03,0:59:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She took a step back, then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.58,0:59:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,another. She closed the double
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.37,0:59:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,doors in silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.39,0:59:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The veranda facing the savanna
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.58,0:59:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,river had a warm late afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.84,0:59:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.67,0:59:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Roena leaned against the cold
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.19,0:59:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,stone parapet,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.21,0:59:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and watched the water dark and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.67,0:59:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.97,0:59:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The reflection of the light
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.50,0:59:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,going away in wide slow bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.71,0:59:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't cry. She felt inside
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.64,0:59:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,her chest a new stillness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.47,1:00:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind that only arrives after
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.02,1:00:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,days that are too long,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.57,1:00:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when the body finally drops its
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.94,1:00:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,guard because it has nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.17,1:00:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,left to put the tension.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.75,1:00:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego found her there ten minutes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.43,1:00:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,later.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.75,1:00:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd washed his face, his suit
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.64,1:00:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was still rumpled. His eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.34,1:00:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,still red settled on her
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.85,1:00:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,before any words and stayed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.40,1:00:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.71,1:00:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As if they needed to confirm
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.94,1:00:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that she was real and that she
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.26,1:00:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,was standing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.41,1:00:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he stopped three steps away. He
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.12,1:00:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't come closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.75,1:00:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Any word he realized would be
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.30,1:00:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,too small. Any sentence would
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.86,1:00:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sound like a clause,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.51,1:00:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd already spent six
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.75,1:00:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,months signing clauses with her
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.23,1:00:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,without asking permission for
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.61,1:00:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.95,1:00:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So he stayed quiet. He just
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.45,1:00:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,stood there, looking at her as
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.11,1:00:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if it were the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.55,1:00:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought him. He said it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.33,1:00:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,last. I brought him. I don't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.18,1:00:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,know how to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.89,1:00:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't thank me. It's not the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.05,1:00:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of thing you thank someone
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.32,1:00:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.95,1:00:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He nodded, a nod that was almost
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.06,1:00:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a bow. The river below kept
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.83,1:00:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,darkening,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.17,1:00:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,indifferent to the weight of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.67,1:00:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that veranda. A girl crossed the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.39,1:00:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sky in a lazy arc.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.85,1:00:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna felt the warmth of his
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.23,1:00:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,body near hers without needing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.65,1:00:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to look to be sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.91,1:01:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was magnetism there. The
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.60,1:01:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,same as always. The same that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.20,1:01:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,had risen up her back on a
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.53,1:01:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,beside him. There was a new
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.27,1:01:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,distance. A distance she decided
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.34,1:01:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to preserve for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.89,1:01:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to sleep alone tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.90,1:01:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, Jego took a second. He
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.04,1:01:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't protest. He didn't make a
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.18,1:01:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,face.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.85,1:01:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't embed any request
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.62,1:01:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,disguised as agreement. That's
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.58,1:01:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,fine. Ruinna turned her face to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.61,1:01:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.15,1:01:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time in six
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.48,1:01:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,months you've given me an answer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.12,1:01:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,without packaging. He almost
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.55,1:01:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,smiled.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.47,1:01:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost. I'm learning. He
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.25,1:01:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,answered. Very low. There was
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.40,1:01:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,exhaustion in his face.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.11,1:01:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was also something
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.71,1:01:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,open she'd never seen there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.25,1:01:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,before. He wasn't the man of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.84,1:01:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,ice.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.45,1:01:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't the man of calculated
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.29,1:01:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,control. He was a man who had
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.01,1:01:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,seen his brother alive after 10
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.85,1:01:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,years and no longer knew what to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.92,1:01:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,do with his own chest. Tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.92,1:01:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will talk. She said,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.67,1:01:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow I'll ask. He said, if
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.62,1:01:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll let me. She nodded. He
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.51,1:01:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,raised his hand toward her face,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.03,1:02:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped halfway and lowered his
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.66,1:02:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,arm. The interrupted gesture
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.13,1:02:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,weighed more than the touch
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.55,1:02:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,would have
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.81,1:02:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna inside understood that he
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.63,1:02:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,had understood. She went down
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.27,1:02:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the veranda stairs without
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.75,1:02:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.65,1:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Feline took her to the house
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.12,1:02:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,near the river. Jego went back
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.70,1:02:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,inside to the family he had
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.12,1:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,forgotten
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.59,1:02:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,how to embrace without a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.90,1:02:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,contract. That night in the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.37,1:02:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen of the house near the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.94,1:02:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,river,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.73,1:02:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna drank a glass of water in
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.42,1:02:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,silence and looked at the phone
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.05,1:02:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,on the table. There were no
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.47,1:02:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,messages. For the first time in
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.20,1:02:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,six months, no one knew where
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.82,1:02:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,she was because no one had been
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.55,1:02:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,put in
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.89,1:02:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,place to know. She turned off
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.39,1:02:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen light and the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.69,1:02:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,darkness arrived with a calm
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.14,1:02:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that seemed
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.71,1:02:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at last deserved. On the other
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.54,1:02:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the city, in a room he
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.38,1:02:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't been in for 10 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.59,1:02:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego quint personally made up
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.34,1:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,his brother's bed, folded the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.08,1:02:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,blanket, opened the window two
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.89,1:02:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fingers to let the air in, and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.76,1:02:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sat on the hallway floor until
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.63,1:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,dawn, with the door a jar
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.19,1:02:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,listening
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.75,1:02:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to kit sleep. Sunday morning
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.48,1:02:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived at the house near the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.26,1:02:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Savannah River, with a low,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.93,1:03:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wary light that came through the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.56,1:03:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,cracks in the curtains, like
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.99,1:03:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,someone asking permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.91,1:03:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruinna was in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.52,1:03:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Barefoot, with a cold mug in her
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.51,1:03:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,hands, she hadn't slept well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.65,1:03:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The two wide bed had felt wide
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.54,1:03:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in a new way, without anger and
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.49,1:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,without peace, only with a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.13,1:03:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,question waiting for its answer
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.73,1:03:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,outside the door. She heard the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.33,1:03:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,engine before she heard the foot
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.98,1:03:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.81,1:03:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A car stopped on the gravel. The
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.40,1:03:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,door closed with the care of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.78,1:03:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who knew the whole house
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.37,1:03:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was listening. Jego appeared in
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.03,1:03:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitchen doorway, with the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.58,1:03:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cream envelope open in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.75,1:03:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He had no jacket. He had the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.15,1:03:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,rumpled shirt of someone who'd
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.64,1:03:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,spent the night sitting on a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.04,1:03:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,hallway
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.39,1:03:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,floor. He stopped two steps from
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.42,1:03:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,her, as if asking permission to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.38,1:03:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,cross that last stretch of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.03,1:03:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,floor. May I? He asked. Ruinna
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.25,1:03:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,nodded. He came. He set the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.25,1:03:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,envelope on the table between
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.40,1:03:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,them,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.89,1:03:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,facing her. The letter was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.39,1:03:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,already unfolded inside. She
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.00,1:03:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,recognized the letter head, the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.79,1:03:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,header,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.19,1:03:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the short paragraph that month's
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.03,1:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier had been intercepted
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.65,1:03:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,before reaching her. They wanted
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.49,1:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you for a series of long
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.00,1:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,reports, Jego said, his voice
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.83,1:04:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,low almost crumpled. In depth
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.65,1:04:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,investigation
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.47,1:04:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,no short deadline. Your by-line
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.41,1:04:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on every piece I read it when it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.41,1:04:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,came. I answered for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.15,1:04:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote with thanks no. I lied
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.90,1:04:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about it every day since. She
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.59,1:04:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at the letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.31,1:04:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at his face. Jego was pale
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.99,1:04:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way different from the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.45,1:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,night of the phone call.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.75,1:04:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That whiteness wasn't fear of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.58,1:04:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what she'd find out. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.29,1:04:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,shame at what he'd done.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.19,1:04:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Ruinna asked without
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.75,1:04:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,sharpness? Just needing to hear
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.69,1:04:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Because I was afraid you'd
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.57,1:04:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,accept,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.39,1:04:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he answered. The pause. Because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.31,1:04:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was even more afraid you'd
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.05,1:04:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,accept and be away some nights.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.43,1:04:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was certain without ever
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.95,1:04:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,having proof that if I let you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.69,1:04:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of my sight, the world would
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.56,1:04:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,carry
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.85,1:04:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,something away. He swallowed
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.64,1:04:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,hard. He knew the size of his
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.50,1:04:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,own mistake. In you love isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.41,1:04:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,protected
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.99,1:04:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by locking a door. In you he'd
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.85,1:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,confused devotion with
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.21,1:04:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,possession. The choice he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.51,1:04:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was always yours. I took it off
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.50,1:04:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the table. I'm giving it back
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.37,1:05:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,now. Ruinna felt her own chin
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.23,1:05:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,tremble without falling into
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.85,1:05:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,tears. She took the phone from
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.58,1:05:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the counter and held it out to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.32,1:05:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.85,1:05:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Start with the guards she asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.74,1:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He took the device without
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.28,1:05:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,arguing. He dialed from memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.61,1:05:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The head of the team's voice
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.16,1:05:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,answered on the second ring.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.70,1:05:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jego spoke while looking at her.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.47,1:05:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull both teams from the house
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.11,1:05:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,today. Pull the two that follow
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.81,1:05:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Pike as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.09,1:05:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, no one follows
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.61,1:05:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone. He heard a question from
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.41,1:05:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the other end that Ruinna didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.21,1:05:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,hear. No, no replacement, no
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.16,1:05:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,exception. Terminate the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.83,1:05:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,contract. He hung up. He handed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.99,1:05:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the phone back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.43,1:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood there waiting for the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.06,1:05:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,next verdict without trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.70,1:05:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,soften anything. Ruinna breathed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.44,1:05:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.55,1:05:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,deep. Something inside her
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.05,1:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,loosened a cord she hadn't
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.56,1:05:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed had been pulled tort for
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.41,1:05:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,months.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.81,1:05:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't smile. It was still
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.86,1:05:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,too early. What do you want for
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.99,1:05:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner? Jego asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.77,1:05:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The question was small and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.27,1:05:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,ridiculous and perfect. She
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.83,1:05:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,laughed before the tear fell. He
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.68,1:05:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,raised his hand
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.55,1:05:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly, touched her cheek like
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.34,1:05:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,someone asking permission and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.06,1:06:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the tear stayed between them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.03,1:06:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Something we make together, she
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.05,1:06:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,answered. He nodded. He said
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.88,1:06:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing more. He stayed. And
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.71,1:06:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,staying.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.85,1:06:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the only big word that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.90,1:06:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,made sense. They spent the day
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.83,1:06:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly. He chopped vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.81,1:06:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With the exaggerated technique
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.40,1:06:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone who'd learned late.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.99,1:06:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She laughed at the way he held
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.58,1:06:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.63,1:06:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kit called from the room Udora
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.08,1:06:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,had prepared at the mansion and
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.59,1:06:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,said he was going to bed early.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.47,1:06:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His voice lighter than the day
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.12,1:06:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,before. Silas sent a dry message
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.87,1:06:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,asking if he was allowed to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.35,1:06:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.33,1:06:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Marlo sent a two minute voice
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.80,1:06:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,memo praising her own sense of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.32,1:06:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,timing for staying quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.01,1:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone from a distance gave
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.58,1:06:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the house near the river. The
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.14,1:06:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,silence it needed to fit back
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.71,1:06:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,into them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.47,1:06:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At night the kitchen went dark
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.85,1:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without anyone turning on the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.19,1:06:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,light.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.47,1:06:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They went up the stairs
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.99,1:06:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,together. It wasn't urgent. It
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.98,1:06:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't ceremonial.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.57,1:06:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hand in hand like two
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.09,1:06:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,people tired of themselves. In
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.73,1:06:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the main bedroom the window was
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.41,1:06:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,open
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.63,1:06:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the river sent in a thin
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.13,1:06:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,breeze that smelled of wet
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.52,1:06:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves. Jego closed the door
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.02,1:06:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with his shoulder
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.93,1:07:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,without hurry. He stood looking
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.56,1:07:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at Roenah for a length of time
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.14,1:07:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,neither of them could count.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.11,1:07:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep down in him. Desire mixed
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.94,1:07:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with a new caution. She was no
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.76,1:07:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,longer just the body he knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.53,1:07:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She was the body that had
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.97,1:07:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to come back even
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.41,1:07:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing the price
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.39,1:07:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that made his hands clumsy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.35,1:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on purpose. Roenah took the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.12,1:07:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,first step. She rested her palm
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.15,1:07:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on his face.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.33,1:07:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,His mouth met her palm before it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.36,1:07:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,met her mouth. A small kiss on
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.25,1:07:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the hand. A request for
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.71,1:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,permission that hadn't been in
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.33,1:07:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,either of their scripts. She
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.85,1:07:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the day old stubble scratch
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.58,1:07:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,her skin.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.45,1:07:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She felt his warm breath. She
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.02,1:07:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the decision to be there
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.58,1:07:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,release from within her chest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.15,1:07:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and become
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.69,1:07:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,body. He rested his forehead on
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.51,1:07:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,hers before kissing her. He
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.10,1:07:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,stayed there for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.13,1:07:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Breath against breath. Inside
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.82,1:07:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,him a sentence formed without
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.51,1:07:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving his mouth. If I have to
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.31,1:07:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,prove it every day I'll prove
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.82,1:07:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it. She too had one that didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.43,1:07:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,come out. I didn't come because
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.04,1:07:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.09,1:07:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,forgave everything. I came
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.57,1:07:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because I want to be here. It
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.22,1:07:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was she who said the outward one
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.05,1:07:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,first.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.71,1:07:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mouth on his jaw. I'm not
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.51,1:08:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,here because I forgave
